{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HrCPBcxFYKAc9TYj44xLoy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both routes work correctly:\n\n- Without header → `stable`\n- With `X-Canary: beta` → `canary`\n\n**What was wrong and what I changed:**\n\n1. **`canary-canary` ingress** had `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always` (a catch-all) instead of `beta`. Changed it to `beta` so only requests with exactly `X-Canary: beta` are routed to the canary backend.\n\n2. **`canary-alt` decoy ingress** (labelled `benchmark.decoy: \"true\"`) was interfering — it claimed `stable-echo` as a `noServer: true` canary backend with header value `beta`. After the first fix introduced a second `beta`-valued canary, the controller could no longer use `stable-echo` as the primary server for `canary.example.com`, breaking all traffic. Deleting the decoy freed `stable-echo` to be the primary backend again, allowing `canary-echo` to be correctly registered as the header-matched alternative."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":393,"cache_read_input_tokens":55035,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":393},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ccdfbad-5007-4997-ad8c-322e5804e21d","uuid":"1ec7cf2d-208a-409e-b5f9-f9feaac91368","request_id":"req_011Cc6h3DBRmp88szRgfoiyb"}
